{{Infobox person |image = Jesse_Nilsson.jpg |caption= | birth_date = December 9, 1977 | birth_place = [[Canada]] | spouse = | death_date = {{death date and age|2003|4|25|1977|12|9}} | death_place = [[North York]], [[Ontario]], Canada | birth_name = Jesse Allan Nilsson | yearsactive = 1993 - 2003 | othername = | website = }} '''Jesse Allan Nilsson''' (December 9, 1977 - April 25, 2003)<ref>[http://www.absolutenow.com/features/deathday0425_1.html absolutenow]</ref> was a [[Canadians|Canadian]] [[actor]] who starred in several television programmes, one of his notable and last parts being Gabriel Patterson on ''[[Adventure Inc.]]''
==Career== Nilsson was active in the dramatic arts from a very young age. He was cast as Eric Singer, one of the central characters in the [[Disney]] TV movie ''[[Model Behavior]]'', which was released on 12 March 2000 in the USA.<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0218121/ Model Behavior (2000) (TV)]</ref> In the television show ''[[Our Hero]]'', which ran from 2000 to 2002, Nilsson played the part of casual-warm and a super-supportive Rollins, an animal rescue guy who "knows way too much about raccoon poop".<ref>[http://www.ourhero.tv/theheroes/index.html THE HEROES cast page showing Jesse Nilsson]</ref>
Nilsson's last major role was as Gabriel Patterson on ''[[Adventure Inc.]]''<ref>[http://www.adventure-inc.net/cast/index.html Fansite dedicated to ADVENTURE INC. Jesse Nilsson bio]</ref> He died from pneumonia-related heart failure on April 25, 2003<ref>{{cite web|URL=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0632235/bio|title=Jesse Nilsson - Biography|access-date=June 10, 2015}}</ref> in [[North York]], [[Ontario]] before the 22nd and final episode, "Trapped", had been broadcast, its original airdate being May 12, 2003. Nilsson was 25 years old. A tribute was added to the last few frames of this episode showing a picture of Nilsson under which was written "In memory of Jesse Nilsson 1977-2003".
